/* CSS Styles */
.card {
    width: 200px;
    padding: 20px;
    border: 5px solid black;
    margin: 10px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    background-color: lightblue;
}

/* Navbar Layout using Flex */
.nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: #333;
    color: white;
}

.links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 20px;
}

lessons.content:
# CSS Grid

Unlike Flexbox, Grid is 2-dimensional (Rows AND Columns simultaneously).

## 1. Setup
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; /* 3 equal columns */
  gap: 10px;
}
```

## 2. The 'fr' Unit
The 'fractional' unit represents a fraction of the available space in the grid container.

lessons.fullProgram:
/* Photo Gallery Grid */
.gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 15px;
}

.item {
    background: #eee;
    height: 150px;
}

lessons.content:
# Responsive Design

Responsive design ensures your site adapts to mobile, tablet, and desktop screens.

## 1. The Meta Viewport
You MUST include this in your `<head>`:
`<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">`

## 2. Media Queries
Allow you to apply CSS only when certain conditions are met.
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .sidebar { 
    display: none; /* Hide on mobile */
  }
}
```

lessons.fullProgram:
/* Responsive Layout Example */
.main-content {
    width: 80%;
    margin: auto;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
    .main-content {
        width: 100%;
        padding: 10px;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 20px; }
}

lessons.content:
# CSS Variables

Variables allow you to store values (like colors or sizes) and reuse them throughout your stylesheet.

## 1. Declaration
Usually declared in the `:root` selector.
```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #ff5733;
  --spacing: 20px;
}
```

## 2. Usage
```css
.btn {
  background-color: var(--primary-color);
  padding: var(--spacing);
}
```

lessons.fullProgram:
:root {
    --bg: #121212;
    --text: #ffffff;
    --accent: #bb86fc;
}

body {
    background-color: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
}

.highlight {
    color: var(--accent);
}

lessons.content:
# Smooth Interactions

## 1. Transitions
Used for simple state changes (like hover).
`transition: background 0.3s ease;`

## 2. Keyframes
Used for complex, multi-stage animations.
```css
@keyframes slideIn {
  from { transform: translateX(-100%); }
  to { transform: translateX(0); }
}

.menu {
  animation: slideIn 0.5s forwards;
}
```

lessons.fullProgram:
/* Pulsing Notification Dot */
.dot {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    background: red;
    border-radius: 50%;
    animation: pulse 1.5s infinite;
}

@keyframes pulse {
    0% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
    50% { transform: scale(1.5); opacity: 0.5; }
    100% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
}
